        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/12–645</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-28">December 28,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="72" xml:id="d752fn1">December 6, <ref target="#pg_1009">p.
                        1009</ref>.</note> of His Excellency the British Ambassador conveying the
                    suggestion of the British Government with respect to publicity for the
                    recommendations of the report of Mr. Pauley to the President has been noted and
                    conveyed to the persons directly concerned.</p>
                <p>No final position on Japanese reparations policies will be announced by the
                    United States Government without prior discussion with the various other
                    interested Governments. The early receipt of the observations of the British
                    Government will be welcomed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
